RACE.FOOTNOTES: GIVE ME THE LUTE went up to duel for command from outside, cleared leaving the backstretch, urged right handed outside the eighth pole and remained comfortably in front under a drive to the wire. JAMMING EDDY stalked the top pair up the backstretch, traveled along the inside then tipped two wide approaching the quarter pole, finished determinedly through the lane and edged PERFECTIONISTIC for second. PERFECTIONISTIC broke well then settled off the pace in the two path, tipped three wide around the bend, chased within striking distance through the lane and got edged for second. MY SUMMER DREAM reserved early on the inside, pushed on while saving ground through the turn, steered out in upper stretch and summoned a mild rally. SUBSIDIZE sat off the pace between rivals at the back, rounded the bend two wide and lacked a rally. WESTWARD LOOK away quickest to clear and crossed over to the inside, dueled with outer rival up the backstretch, ceded command approaching the turn, chased along the rail to the stretch and weakened. MONGOLIAN LEGEND raced outside a pair of rivals at the back, trailed two wide into the lane and had little left for the stretch run.

NEON LIGHTS (IRE) steadied cautiously early and moved inside, coaxed along the rail in range through the turn, lacked room from the top of the stretch to the eighth pole, altered out midstretch to unleash a rally but was outkicked by the winner. PETCOFF got bumped on both sides crossing the dirt, chased three then two wide on the turn, launched a bid while drifting in and brushing rival in the lane and was outfinished in deep stretch. VEGAS BURNER broke well from outside, came in and bumped rival crossing the dirt, cleared after and moved inside, met the challenge from PIONEER PRINCE on the turn, dueled down the lane, brushed with that rival midstretch and faltered late. PIONEER PRINCE bumped hard crossing over the dirt with outer rival, chased after the pacesetter up the backstretch, moved out and launched a bid on the turn, fought between rivals while getting brushed and faltered late. SIX MAGPIES (IRE) broke a step slow, traveled along the inside at the back, made progress through the turn, tipped out into the lane, forced to check midstretch and was not persevered with after. MOBE TOWN got sandwiched crossing the dirt early then put tight and steadied shortly after, rounded the bend in the two path and could not rally. CLASSICAL got bumped between rivals crossing over the dirt, chased four wide around the bend and came up empty. THERE WAS A PAIR OF STEWARDS' INQUIRYS INVOLVING THE SEVENTH RACE. FIRST THE STEWARDS RULED THAT VEGAS BURNER BE DISQUALIFIED FROM FOURTH TO LAST FOR COMING OVER AND CAUSING A CHAIN REACTION CROSSING THE DIRT. THEY ALSO REVIEWED THE INCIDENT BETWEEN NEON LIGHTS (IRE) AND SIX MAGPIES (IRE) MIDSTRETCH AND RULED THAT THERE WOULD BE NO CHANGE.
